cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CR

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual kin-based problems. It may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it involves large-scale, multi-track evaluation. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses search and retrieval of missing children. Machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) are also possible sub-categories as the paper mentions benchmark results and technical background.
